Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6.Heat the oil in a casserole dish over a medium heat. Add the onions and garlic and cook until softened, stirring occasionally.Stir in the plums, ginger, chicken, soy sauce, sugar and 100ml/3½fl oz water. Cover with a lid and bring to the boil.Transfer the dish to the oven and bake for 30–40 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the plums have collapsed into a sauce.  Taste and season with more soy sauce if necessary.Meanwhile, cook the rice according to the packet instructions. Leave with the lid on until ready to serve.Meanwhile, place the broccoli in a metal colander over a pan of simmering water. Cover with a lid and steam until just tender. Alternatively, cook using a steamer.Serve the rice with the plum chicken and broccoli. Scatter over the coriander.